CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Financing Act – Fair Campaign Financing Fund – Distributions
3 FOR the purpose of altering the earliest date on which the State Board of Elections may
4 begin making distributions from the Fair Campaign Financing Fund; and generally
5 relating to distributions from the Fair Campaign Financing Fund.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
7 Article – Election Law
8 Section 15–102(a) and (f)
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
11 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
12 Article – Election Law
13 Section 15–107(a)
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Election Law
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
