2 HOUSE BILL 260
1 15–102.
2 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
3 (f) “Fund” means the Fair Campaign Financing Fund.
4 15–107.
5 (a) (1) In accordance with subsection (c) of this section and regulations
6 adopted by the State Board, the State Board shall authorize distribution of money in the
7 Fund on a continuing basis on certification that the qualifications under § 15–104 of this
8 title have been met.
9 (2) Distributions shall begin not earlier than [January] JULY 1 of the year
10 [of] BEFORE the election.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2026.
